It is agreed that:
- The LICENSEE will exercise all reasonable and prudent care to avoid disclosing the identity of any individual or institution referenced in the provided data in any publication or other communication.
- The LICENSEE will not share access to the data with anyone else.
- The LICENSEE will exercise all reasonable and prudent care to maintain the physical and electronic security of the data.
- If the LICENSEE finds information within the data that he or she believes might permit the identification of any individual or institution, the LICENSEE will privately report this information promptly, citing the location of the specific information in question.
- The LICENSEE will use the data for the sole purpose of lawful use in scientific research and no other.
Either party may terminate this agreement at any time, but the LICENSEE's obligations concerning the data shall continue after termination.